    "prompt": "<p><img alt=\"The figure shows electrons moving from left to right in a tube. The electrons travel through a magnetic field created by a horseshoe magnet. The magnetic field is directed upward. The electrons reach a display screen that has vertical and horizontal axes that meet at the center of the screen. The top of the vertical axis is labeled a the bottom of the vertical axis is labeled b, the left end of the horizontal axis is labeled c, and the right end of the horizontal axis is labeled d. \" height=\"210\" src=\"/images/db7162cac6c370d34e9277050ac2a686.png\" width=\"355\"></p>\n\n<p>A horizontal electron beam in an oscilloscope is aimed at the center of the display screen, as shown in the diagram above. A C-shaped magnet is placed around the oscilloscope, producing a vertical magnetic field <strong>B</strong>, which is perpendicular to the beam. Which way, if any, will the beam be deflected by the magnetic field?</p>\n",
